id: pm-dzcx
title: Dedup private Levenshtein implementations onto shared OSA helper
description: "Two files reimplement plain Levenshtein instead of importing the shared OSA Damerau-Levenshtein helper (src/core/shared/levenshtein.ts, levenshteinDistanceWithinLimit): (1) src/core/store/item-store.ts:193 'levenshtein' used by buildDidYouMeanSuggestions for item-ID did-you-mean; (2) src/core/extensions/extension-capability-aliases.ts:61 'levenshteinDistance' used by suggestKnownExtensionCapability. Besides duplication, both copies miss the transposition-cost-1 upgrade shipped in PR #78, so ID/capability typo suggestions are weaker than flag/command suggestions. Fix: replace both with the shared limited helper (item-store uses a dynamic limit max(3, len/2) so call with that limit; capability suggester is unbounded best-match, can iterate limits or add a non-limited export). Evidence: grep -rln levenshtein src/ shows 7 importers of the shared module + these 2 private copies."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 3
